res22: org.apache.spark.sql.SparkSession = org.apache.spark.sql.SparkSession@7f1193d4

df: org.apache.spark.sql.DataFrame = [time: date, amount: float]

paragraphs.text:
%sql 
select time, amount, 
IF(MONTH(time) = 7 or MONTH(time) = 8 , amount, null) as holidays, 
IF(MONTH(time) = 12 and DAY(time) <= 28, amount, null) as christmas, 
IF(MONTH(time) = 6 and DAY(time) <= 23, amount, null) as fathersDay, 
IF((time > '2014-03-01' and time < '2014-03-17') OR (time > '2015-10-04' and time < '2015-10-21') OR (time > '2016-09-04' and time < '2016-09-20'), amount, null) as discount from sales

paragraphs.title: Create DateTransformer to transform a date to exploitable features (Year, Month, day, day of week...)
paragraphs.text:
class SimpleDateTransformer(asVector: Boolean = false) extends org.apache.spark.ml.Transformer {
    import org.apache.spark.ml.Transformer
    import org.apache.spark.ml.linalg.{SQLDataTypes, Vectors}
    import org.apache.spark.ml.param.ParamMap
    import org.apache.spark.sql.types._
    import org.apache.spark.sql.{DataFrame, Dataset}
    import org.apache.spark.sql.functions._
    import java.time._
    import spark.implicits._
    
    val dayofweek = udf{date: java.sql.Date => date.toLocalDate.getDayOfWeek.getValue}
    
    override def transform(dataset: Dataset[_]): DataFrame = {
      dataset.toDF()
        .withColumn("year", year($"time"))
        .withColumn("month", month($"time"))
        .withColumn("dayOfMonth", dayofmonth($"time"))
        .withColumn("dayOfWeek", dayofweek($"time"))
        .withColumn("weekOfYear", weekofyear($"time"))
        .withColumn("dayOfYear", dayofyear($"time"))
    }

    override def copy(extra: ParamMap): Transformer = new SimpleDateTransformer(asVector)

    override def transformSchema(schema: StructType): StructType = schema.add("year", DataTypes.IntegerType)
                                                                         .add("month", DataTypes.IntegerType)
                                                                         .add("dayOfMonth", DataTypes.IntegerType)
                                                                         .add("dayOfWeek", DataTypes.IntegerType)
                                                                         .add("weekOfYear", DataTypes.IntegerType)
                                                                         .add("dayOfYear", DataTypes.IntegerType)

    override val uid: String = "dateTransformer"
  }

val simplePipeline = new Pipeline().setStages(Array(new SimpleDateTransformer()))

val dfWithIdx: DataFrame = df.dfZipWithIndex()

simplePipeline.fit(df).transform(dfWithIdx).createOrReplaceTempView("simpleFeatures")

paragraphs.title: Features
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.VectorAssembler
  
  val assembler = new VectorAssembler()
    .setInputCols(Array("id","year","month","dayOfMonth","dayOfWeek","weekOfYear","dayOfYear"))
    .setOutputCol("features")

  val limitDate = "2016-06-01"
  val trainingData = dfWithIdx.filter(dfWithIdx("time").lt(lit(limitDate)))

  val rf = new RandomForestRegressor()
    .setNumTrees(40) //Reduce variance 40 
    .setMaxDepth(25) //Reduce bias 25
    .setLabelCol("amount")
    .setFeaturesCol("features")

  val pipeline = new Pipeline().setStages(Array(new SimpleDateTransformer(), assembler, rf))

  // Train the model.
  val model = pipeline.fit(trainingData)

  // Make predictions.
  val predictions = model.transform(dfWithIdx).registerTempTable("simpleForecast")

val assemblerSeasonality = new VectorAssembler()
    .setInputCols(Array("month","dayOfMonth","dayOfWeek","weekOfYear","dayOfYear")) //Remove Random Forest unknown/trend features (id, year)
    .setOutputCol("features")
    
  val rfStationary = new RandomForestRegressor()
    .setNumTrees(50) //Reduce variance
    .setMaxDepth(25) //Reduce bias
    .setLabelCol("amountStationary")
    .setFeaturesCol("features")

  val pipelineStationary = new Pipeline().setStages(Array(new SimpleDateTransformer(), assemblerSeasonality, rfStationary))

  // Train the model.
  val trainingDataStationary = dfStationary.filter(dfStationary("time").lt(lit(limitDate)))
  val modelStationary = pipelineStationary.fit(trainingDataStationary)

  // Make predictions.
  val predictionStationary = modelStationary.transform(dfStationary)
  predictionStationary.createOrReplaceTempView("predictionStationary")
